goran blix republics of letters a journal for the study of knowledge politics and the arts link to arcade home editors blog issues rss contact admin login home goran blix goran blix email website is an assistant professor of french at princeton university he specializes in literature and cultural history of nineteenth century france his research interests center on the poetics of historiography narratives of archeology the social uses of memory and the formation of national identity he has published papers on zola balzac and michelet and is currently preparing a book based on his dissertation which analyzed the nineteenth century reception of pompeii fora between experience and experiment limits of the atlantic republican tradition on sovereignty rethinking the republic of letters the leland stanford jr university seal issn 2159 1873
